[Name] GTK-Layer-Shell
[Summary] Library to create Wayland desktop components using the Layer Shell protocol
[Description]
A library to write GTK applications that use Layer Shell. Layer Shell is a Wayland protocol
for desktop shell components, such as panels, notifications and wallpapers. You can use it
to anchor your windows to a corner or edge of the output, or stretch them across the entire output.
[License] GPL3, LGPL3, MIT
[Homepage] https://github.com/wmww/gtk-layer-shell
